lass?</span><hr size=1> Lets look at the following numbers:<br>
(note I play midguard chars 99% of my time)<br>
<br>
Albion has 35.6% of all the rps (1869.2 million)<br>
Hibernia has 33% of all the rps (1729.2 million)<br>
Midguard has 31.4% of all the rps (1648.2 million)<br>
<br>
Those numbers are rounded to the nearest hundred thousand rp points accross all the servers except mordred and  Pendragon.<br>
<br>
Ok so here we would say that alb clearly needs to be nerfed.  Hib is okay and midguard needs help.  Remember we are talking a difference of 4.1%.  That's a lot given that you are talking about a difference of 221 _million_ rps.  <br>
<br>
I know people will say wait albion has more people and that's the difference.  I am willing to bet that that's correct.  There are servers where alb is killing the others and there are servers where mid is killing the others and there are servers where hib is killing the others.<br>
<br>
From the pattern I saw when I looked at servers and totals in rps I would suggest this:<br>
<br>
I think the different realms win and lose based on population differences.  Thus, the problems people are experiencing are based on population differences more than anything else.<br>
<br>
We need to push mythic hard to put in something to ballance population differences among the servers.  Until then you just can't judge rps as a measure of anything.  It's not fair at all and I would guess from the fights I have seen that this is the single most unballancing feature in the game.<br>
<br>
How can you ballance classes or realms or ANYTHING if you have 20% in one realm and 40% of the people playing in another realm.  It will never be entirely equal but right now why would you join a gimped realm to spend days of your life leveling to be frustrated..why would you knowingly do that to yourself? <br>
<br>
The forces that control populations all point towards an increase in the differences not a decrease.  There is currently NO incentive to join an underpopulated realm..unless you are the odd hero who likes the underdog and seeks thats situation out I guess.<br>
<br>
I think mythic should put in an xp bonus system based on the number of active characters 40+ in each realm.<br>
<br>
For example, if one realm has 50% of the active characters over 40 then they gain xp the same as they do right now.  However if one realm drops below 33.3 percent they get a bonus based on that difference.  Again the xp bonus should be bigger if the population difference is bigger and thus smaller if the difference is smaller.<br>
<br>
These differences and the bonuses that are in effect should be clearly posted on the web page, thus allowing people to make an informed choice about the server and realm that they play. <br>
<br>
This would provide an incentive to join underpopulated realms and not hurt the populated realms.  People could still play with their friends.  <br>
<br>
I can't see a loser here.  The realms that are dominant have to be bored.  They need people to fight.  The realms that are losing need more people and certainly need more people 40+.<br>
<br>
In the end as the population ballances out I think patterns would begin to appear.  Then you could look at these patterns and ballance the classes appropriately.<br>
<br>
Mel<br>
<br>
Melanu.<br>
