<br>
all realm points do,is show whos active,as a player base,as a guild,and as a realm on every server.<br>
<br>
i also believe the issue of class vs class balance,is the basic root of the problem. people dont want to be inferior to other classes in any fashion,this is what caused the sb issues here,and will cause the infiltrators to get nerfed at some point in time.<br>
<br>
casters will most likely see nerfs coming up sometime in the future as well,as possible nerfs on mez/stun again. all this is due to mythic searching endlessly for class balance,and they are unable to achieve it.<br>
<br>
the only way to compensate for this is to focus on realm balance. this means you have to have classes that are stronger in one realm then others,classes that have more magic in others,and classes that are a good mixture of both.<br>
<br>
right now,the reason albion is all powerful,is due to numbers,and basically thats because of the class variety,and the fact that many classes are equal to or better then the speciality classes in the other 2 realms,who were suppose to be specalized realms.<br>
<br>
i like your ideas,but i honestly dont think they will accomplish what you intend for them to,because even if you have 200 mids all level 50,on a server where you still have 450 albsions 40-50,the albions are almost always going to do better overall.<br>
<br>
the easiest way to solve population imbalance is to honestly shut down about 1/3 -1/2 of the game servers,and combine all the accounts into seperate servers. this will increase the player bse by a large margin.<br>
<br>
it wont solve the imbalance per say,but what it will do,is give realms that are underpopulated on the server more people overall,and more of a chance to compete,or at least defend there realms.<br>
